{
  "doc_id": "3517",
  "text": "The carbon isotopic composition (δ 13 C) of trees is influenced by carbon isotopic composition (δ 13 C) of atmospheric CO 2 , diffusion of CO 2 through stomata, and enzymatic discrimination during the irreversible step of CO 2 fixation [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] Roden 2008 ). The carbon isotopic composition in plant varies with water stress and solar radiation and has been correlated inter alia with rainfall amount, vapor pressure deficit, canopy position, and hydraulic conductivity associated with tree height [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] .",
